The UK government is currently holding a Covid-19 briefing, and we will update the total number of cases in the UK in the next update.

Singapore reported 657 new cases of Covid-19, of which 10 are Singaporeans and PRs. An 86-year-old female Singaporean became the 18th person to die of the virus in Singapore, six days after being confirmed with Covid-19, on April 27. [Please see Page 2 for Singapore's Covid-19 situation.]

.
